        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 24,
          "y": 72,
          "content": "karpathy.github.io  ·  Nov 21, 2015",
          "fontSize": 10,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "rgba(200,192,228,0.45)",
          "letterSpacing": 0.1,
          "lineHeight": 1.35,
          "width": 280,
          "align": "left",
          "opacity": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 24,
          "y": 94,
          "content": "The Unreasonable\nEffectiveness of\nRecurrent Neural\nNetworks",
          "fontSize": 26,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "700",
          "fill": "#E8E4F0",
          "letterSpacing": -1,
          "lineHeight": 1.2,
          "width": 342,
          "align": "left",
          "opacity": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 24,
          "y": 228,
          "content": "There's something magical about Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs). I still remember when I trained my first recurrent network for Image Captioning. Within a few dozen minutes of training my first baby model...",
          "fontSize": 14,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#E8E4F0",
          "letterSpacing": -0.1,
          "lineHeight": 1.65,
          "width": 342,
          "align": "left",
          "opacity": 0.88
        },
        {
          "type": "RECTANGLE",
          "x": 20,
          "y": 348,
          "width": 350,
          "height": 54,
          "fill": "rgba(123,94,167,0.18)",
          "cornerRadius": 4,
          "opacity": 1,
          "stroke": null,
          "strokeWidth": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "RECTANGLE",
          "x": 20,
          "y": 348,
          "width": 3,
          "height": 54,
          "fill": "#9B7EC8",
          "cornerRadius": 2,
          "opacity": 1,
          "stroke": null,
          "strokeWidth": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 30,
          "y": 356,
          "content": "...the results were so immediately interesting, I felt compelled to investigate them further by writing this post.",
          "fontSize": 14,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#E8E4F0",
          "letterSpacing": -0.1,
          "lineHeight": 1.55,
          "width": 332,
          "align": "left",
          "opacity": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "RECTANGLE",
          "x": 24,
          "y": 412,
          "width": 342,
          "height": 46,
          "fill": "rgba(62,207,207,0.14)",
          "cornerRadius": 8,
          "opacity": 1,
          "stroke": null,
          "strokeWidth": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 34,
          "y": 424,
          "content": "◈",
          "fontSize": 13,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#3ECFCF",
          "letterSpacing": -0.2,
          "lineHeight": 1.35,
          "width": 18,
          "align": "left",
          "opacity": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 52,
          "y": 421,
          "content": "Kern connected this to \"Wonder as epistemic signal\" from 3 days ago",
          "fontSize": 11,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#3ECFCF",
          "letterSpacing": -0.1,
          "lineHeight": 1.42,
          "width": 302,
          "align": "left",
          "opacity": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "x": 24,
          "y": 470,
          "content": "I'll try to convince you that this is true with three relatively minor examples. The first will be a character-level language model and the second and third will be handwriting generation.",
          "fontSize": 14,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#E8E4F0",
          "letterSpacing": -0.1,
          "lineHeight": 1.65,
          "width": 342,
          "align": "left",
